@node "CanDo_MPButtons" "CanDo MainPanel's Buttons"
   The leftmost section of the Main Panel consists of the @{fg highlight}Browse/Design@{fg text}
switch.  This switch allows the user to either test the application,
@{fg highlight}Browse@{fg text} it, or edit the application, @{fg highlight}Design@{fg text} it.

  @{" Browse Mode " link "CanDo_MPBrowseDesignMode"} @{" Design Mode " link "CanDo_MPBrowseDesignMode"}

   The next section is the card control system.  At the top of the section
are two buttons that allow you to edit the current card and its window.

  @{" Edit Card " link "CanDo_Card_Editor"} @{" Edit Window " link "CanDo_Window_Editor"}

   Below these two buttons are five more buttons.  These allow you to
navigate around your deck.

   [ Previous Card ] [ Goto Card ] [    Next Card ]
   [ First Card           ] [           Last Card ]

   The middle, and largest, section is the object control system.  The
first three buttons control object creation and manipulation.

  @{" Add              " link "CanDo_MPAddEditCopy"}
  @{" Edit             " link "CanDo_MPAddEditCopy"}
  @{" Copy             " link "CanDo_MPCopyPaste"}
   
   To the right of these three buttons are twelve buttons that make up the
primary objects available for CanDo decks.

   Button             Field            
   Proportional       Memo/List        
   Menu               RightMouseButton 
   KeyInput           Timer            
   Disk               Sound            
   ARexx              BrushAnim        
   Error              Routines         *

   The list of Xtra object tools is at the far right of the Main Panel.

   BookMark         *
   ConfigCanDo      *
   DosNotify        
   GamePort         
   LastBookMark     *
   MenuRender       
   ObjectLayer      *
   SuperDuper       *
  @{" SuperMover      " link "CanDo_SuperMover_Editor"}*
   
   The items above with an '*' are actually tools, not object editors.
Tools are usually used to modify existing objects or scripts.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_MPShortCutKeys" "CanDo's Shortcut Keys"
@{fg highlight}Control-F4@{fg text}

   Save the deck.  This only works if the deck has been saved at least
once, or was loaded, so that it has a file name.

@{fg highlight}Control-F8@{fg text} 

   Scroll the screen up/down.  This is the same as pressing the scroll
button in the upper right corner of the CanDo screen.

@{fg highlight}Control-F9@{fg text} 

   Send CanDo and User screens to the back of all other screens.
   
@{fg highlight}Control-Shift-F9@{fg text} 

   Send only the CanDo screen to the back of all other screens.
  
@{fg highlight}Control-F10@{fg text} 

   Bring the CanDo and User screens in front of all other screens.
   
@{fg highlight}Control-Shift-F10@{fg text} 

   Bring the CanDo screen in front of all other screens.
 
If ExpertMode is enabled then this additional key is available.

@{fg highlight}Control-F3@{fg text} 

   Save the user's window as an ILBM picture to the current directory.  A
specific directory can be defined using the ConfigCanDo utility tool.

@endnode

