@endnode

@node "CanDo_MPTitleBar" "CanDo MainPanel's Titlebar"
@{b}Deck: UnnamedDeck,  Card: Card_1                    CanDo.1 v2.5x/2.5x@{ub}
   
@{fg highlight}Deck: Unnamed@{fg text}

   The currently loaded deck's name is shown in the titlebar of the CanDo
main panel.

@{fg highlight}Card: Card.1@{fg text}

   The current card's name is shown in the titlebar of the CanDo main
panel.

@{fg highlight}CanDo.1@{fg text}

   If you are running more than one copy of CanDo the number following
the period will change.  1 means the first CanDo, 2 means the second, etc.

@{fg highlight}v2.5x/2.5x@{fg text}

   The first version number is the version of the CanDo you are running.
The second version number shows the version of the CanDo.Library running.
   
   The '/' character between the two version numbers will change to a '*'
if the current deck has any changes that have not been saved.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_MPDeck" "CanDo MainPanel's Deck Menu"
@{fg highlight}Deck/New@{fg text}

   Erase the current deck and load the default deck.

@{fg highlight}Deck/Open@{fg text}

   Erase the current deck and load a selected deck.  This will open the
file requester.

@{fg highlight}Deck/Save@{fg text}

   Quickly save the current deck.  If the deck has not been saved before
then the file requester will open.

@{fg highlight}Deck/Save As...@{fg text}

   Save the current deck to a selected file.  This will open the file
requester.

@{fg highlight}Deck/Quit@{fg text}

   Shut down CanDo.  If CanDo notices that the deck has not been saved you
will be asked if you really want to quit.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_MPCard" "CanDo MainPanel's Card Menu"
@{fg highlight}Card/Goto/Card...@{fg text}

   This allows you select which card in the deck to goto.

@{fg highlight}Card/Goto/First@{fg text}

   Goto the first card in the deck.  If you are already on the first card
then you will simply goto it again.

@{fg highlight}Card/Goto/Previous@{fg text}

   Goto the previous card in the deck.  If you are on the first card in the
deck you will end up on the last card of the deck.

@{fg highlight}Card/Goto/Next@{fg text}

   Goto the next card in the deck.  If you are on the last card in the deck
you will end up on the first card of the deck.

@{fg highlight}Card/Goto/Last@{fg text}

   Goto the last card in the deck.  If you are already on the last card
then you will simply goto it again.

@{fg highlight}Card/Edit Card...@{fg text}

   This will allow you to manipulate and create cards.

   See Also: @{" Card Editor " link "CanDo_Card_Editor"} and @{" Card's Manager " link "CanDo_EditAll"}.

@{fg highlight}Card/Edit Window...@{fg text}

   This will allow you to manipulate the current card's window.

   See Also: @{" Window Editor " link "CanDo_Window_Editor"}.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_MPMisc" "CanDo MainPanel's Misc. Menu"
@{fg highlight}CanDo v2.5x Info...@{fg text}

   This series of requesters gives you Inovatronics' address and CanDo's
authors.
   
@{fg highlight}More Info...@{fg text}

   These requesters tell you about your computer, the current deck and more
version information.

@{fg highlight}Copy/Paste Info...@{fg text}

   This requester will tell you what is in the copy/paste buffer.

   See Also: @{" Copy/Paste System " link "CanDo_MPCopyPaste"}.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_MPExpert" "CanDo MainPanel's Expert Menu"

This menu is only available when ExpertMode is turned on.

@{fg highlight}Flush Buffers@{fg text}

   Flushes all the current deck's buffers.  This may cause the card to
redraw its window.  This will only flush buffers that are not in use.  To
get rid of buffers currently in use you will have to reload the deck.
   
@{fg highlight}Dispose Variables@{fg text}

   Clears all the current deck's variables.  This is a useful way to change
your deck back to its initially loaded state.

@{fg highlight}Clear Window@{fg text}

   This will cause the card to redraw its window.

@{fg highlight}Save Card Info...@{fg text}

   This requester will show what the filename will be if you save the
current card using the @{" Control-F3 " link "CanDo_MPShortCutKeys"} key.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_MPBrowseDesignMode" "CanDo MainPanel's Modes"
@{fg highlight}Design mode@{fg text}

   When in this mode you are allowed to add and/or edit the objects and
cards of the current deck.  When in Design mode all activity in the current
deck is paused.
   
@{fg highlight}Browse mode@{fg text}

   This mode lets you test your deck without leaving CanDo.  If an error
occurs while in browse mode you will be taken directly to the script editor
so that you can correct the error.
   
@{fg highlight}SuperBrowse mode@{fg text}

   This mode is like Browse mode except that CanDo shuts down its MainPanel,
allowing the availability of more memory for your deck.  When in this mode a
small window will appear on the Workbench.  Simply double-click in this
window to exit SuperBrowse mode.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_MPCopyPaste" "CanDo MainPanel's Copy/Paste System"

   The @{fg highlight}Copy@{fg text} mode for objects allows you to select an object to copy.
When in copy mode you can select any object from the current card's window
or select one of the object types from the main panel.  If you select one
of the object types from the main panel a requester will appear, allowing
you to select the object to copy.  Some object types only support one
object per card so no additional requester will appear.

   You can copy the current card or its window by selecting either the
@{" Edit Card Button " link "CanDo_MPButtons"} or the @{" Edit Window Button " link "CanDo_MPButtons"} when in copy mode.

   You can use the @{" Copy/Paste Info... " link "CanDo_MPMisc"} menu item to show the type of
object currently in the copy buffer.
   
   The @{fg highlight}Paste@{fg text} menu item will paste the copied object into the current card.
If there is a card in the copy buffer then is will be pasted into the
current deck at the end.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_MPAddEditCopy" "CanDo MainPanel's Add, Edit and Copy buttons"
@{fg highlight}Add@{fg text}

   This mode allows you to add objects to the current card.  When in this
mode simply select the button for the object type you want to add and a
reqester will guide you through the process of adding the object.

   Some of the buttons on the Main Panel are not used for adding objects,
but are used for editing the current deck or card.  These buttons do
the same thing in both the "Add" and "Edit" modes.

@{fg highlight}Edit@{fg text}

   This mode allows you to edit objects in the current card.  There are two
ways of selecting which object you want to edit:  1) click directly on the
object in the current card's window, which will take you directly to the
object's editor, or 2) click on the button in the Main Panel for the type of
object you want to edit, then select the specific object from the @{" EditAll " link "CanDo_EditAll"}
list.

@{fg highlight}Copy@{fg text}

   Refer to:  @{" Copy/Paste System " link "CanDo_MPCopyPaste"}.

@endnode
   



